args: There. I've finished cutting the wood.
Hello, Ranzal! I didn't hear you there.
Cuttin' up wood in mid-air is no mean feat.
Especially with a blade.\nReal impressive stuff.
I've swung weapons from the smithy\nsince I was a little girl.
So I know how to use all of them,\nalthough blades seem to come\nmost naturally to me.
I love being able to slice things up\nlike it's nothing! Hee hee!
Guess that's why it don't seem\nlike no big thing to ya.
Ack! I just remembered I'm supposed\nto help prep for tonight's meal!
Can't wait to see whatcha do with\nveggies after seein' ya go to town\non those logs.
My mise en place will be done\nmise en FAST! See ya, Ranzal!
Nope. No idea what that meant.
That's all right. I'm simply glad to have\nthe help of both you and Luca today.
Just tell us what to do, boss!
Rena, can I have you peel the potatoes?
While you're doing that, Luca and I will\nhead to the vegetable garden and get\nthe other produce we'll need.
...We're back! Behold my mighty\nmountain of veggies!
Yes, I fear we may have harvested\nrather too many.
Oh gosh, I'm so sorry!\nI didn't know you were back.
The kitchen is no place to be swingin' a\nblade around! The heck are you thinkin'?!
Why, I'm peeling potatoes, of course!
You have done a fine job,\nbut that is hardly the point.
Why are you not using the kitchen\nknife that is right by your side\ninstead of that...blade?
Because this is so much easier!
She IS kind of amazing with that thing.
But, uh, didn't you use that same blade\nto dice up a load of fiends yesterday?
She has used it to ＂dice fiends＂\nfor as long as she's been with us.
The kitchen is no place for a utensil\nthat is dripping with fiend blood!
Pffft! I wiped it off, you guys!
Boy, I'm starvin'! What time is din...\nUh, hey there, guys. Why do you\nall look like you're about to fight?
Rena is insisting on using her blade for\ncooking, so I had to give her a lecture.
Heh. Yeah, that sounds like my sister.
Still, maybe try to go easy on her.
And why would I do that?
Because I remember when my dad\ntold me about why Rena loves blades.
Our mom was pretty frail and sickly\nwhile we were growin' up.
Dad's work picked up around then,\nso he couldn't pitch in much.
So that's why Rena started helpin'\nwith housework at a young age.
She was just a kid, so she screwed a\nlot of stuff up—but she tried her best.
She'd ask Mom how to do somethin',\nthen work at it until she got it right.
And that's when she discovered blades.
I await with bated breath you bringing\nthese two disparate plotlines together.
Well, we had a lot of 'em layin' around\nthe smithy. They're sharp and light and\neasy to cut with. ...Ya know. Blades!

Anyway, they were somethin' even a kid
could wrap her head around, and soon
Rena was runnin' around usin' blades
every chance she got.

Hmm. I suppose if I look at this from
the perspective of a child—and perhaps
squint a bit—it makes a certain amount
of sense.
*sniff* Aw, that's such a moving story.
Stop crying as if this story\ndoes not directly involve you!
*sigh* Very well. I will do what I can\nto overlook her...blade fetish.
You may use your blade, Rena—\nbut only within reason!
With Cleo's permission to use her blade secured,\nRena set about to wield it at every opportunity.
There! Now each of you have half.
Your hair is looking pretty shaggy lately.
Ha ha! Looking sharp, my young friend!
I saw you with some hussy earlier,\nand don't you dare deny it!
Oh, right. Because guys your age TOTALLY\nwalk around arm-in-arm with their sister.
She was just messin' around! I swear!
Hmm... It probably can, let me consider\nmy options for a second.
Wait, SERIOUSLY?! ...Nooo, I'm sorry!\nI'll never cheat again! Don't hurt me!
Ah ha! The truth comes out at last!\n...And my blade can DEFINITELY solve this.
No, I'll let him off the hook this time.\nBut if it happens again, I'm coming to you.
Hey! Cleo said you could use that blade\nWITHIN REASON, remember?!
Everyone is freakin' terrified of you now!
If you start ruining relations with everyone\nwho lives near the Halidom, you won't be\nable to stay here.
I hereby ban you from swingin' your\nblade around for a while.
There's an ideal tool for every situation...\nand it ain't always a damn blade!
*sniff* C-can I still sleep with my baby?
Uhhh, we still talkin' 'bout the blade here?\nYeah, I...guess that's okay.
What about taking it on my morning walk?\nI can't stay in shape otherwise!
No. You'll scare everyone to death.
Can I take it shopping? People always\ngive me discounts whenever I—
